                <h1>Unraveling the History of Cocaine</h1>
                <p>Cocaine, derived from the coca plant, has a rich history dating back to ancient civilizations in South America, where indigenous peoples used it for its stimulant properties. In the 19th century, it gained popularity in Europe and America, often found in tonics and drinks. However, its addictive nature led to regulation and stigma, shaping its modern status.</p>
